The paper deals with the design and analysis of Space-Time Block Codes (STBCs) which are primarily studied in the Information Theory (cs.IT) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of matrix representations of Clifford algebras, which is a topic in the Algebraic Geometry (cs.AG) sub-category. However, since the focus of the paper is on STBCs, it is more likely to be classified under cs.IT. The paper also discusses the concept of decoding complexity, which is a topic in the Signal Processing (cs.SI) and Information Theory and Probability (cs.ITP) sub-categories. The paper also presents achievable upper bounds on the rate of the codes, which is a topic in the Learning (cs.LG) and Numerical Analysis (cs.NA) sub-categories. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories for this paper are cs.IT, cs.SI, cs.ITP, cs.LG, and cs.NA.
